{
  "answer": "In *Manusmṛti* Chapter 3, Manu first introduces the topic of the eight forms of marriage in verse 3.20.[^1] He then lists all eight forms explicitly **in order** in the very next verse (3.21): *Brāhma*, *Daiva*, *Ārṣa*, *Prājāpatya*, *Āsura*, *Gāndharva*, *Rākṣasa*, and *Paiśāca*.[^2] He proceeds to describe each of them in sequence across verses 3.27–3.34 (one verse per form, matching the order above).[^3]\n\n[^1]: [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-36d967/).\n\n[^2]: [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-b07c61/).\n\n[^3]: [paragraphs](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-93ddb7/#p-7c3179/#p-831e2c/#p-c50f0a/#p-4b354a/#p-beb0f2/#p-2f28cf/#p-ca03b2/).",
